CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 14, 1959, page A3, reads: "Second Prize - Harriet Smith, second-prize winner in the NAACP Youth Council talent show, displays a look of satisfaction for her $50 Savings Bond. The show was held March 6 at Westinghouse High School. Her winning selection was 'For Your Love.' - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Harriet Smith wearing eyeglasses and dark belted dress with scoop neck, holding savings bond, standing against light colored wall in Westinghouse High School Auditorium, for tNAACP Youth Council talent show
